19:["$","div",null,{"className":"section-block","children":[["$","h3",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0},"children":"How to fill item specifics correctly"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Go to your listing editor and fill in every field eBay offers, even the ones that seem obvious or redundant. If eBay asks for \"Country/Region of Manufacture\" and you don't know, your best guess is better than leaving it blank."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Use eBay's recommended values when they appear as dropdown options — these are the values that Cassini recognizes and can index correctly. Typed-in custom values are less reliably indexed."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":0},"children":"For high-value items (electronics, collectibles, clothing), eBay has started requiring item specifics and will suppress listings that lack them. Getting ahead of this is important."}]]}]
1a:["$","h2",null,{"children":"3. Category Selection Changes Everything"}]
1b:["$","p",null,{"children":"eBay's category tree is deep. A vintage camera can live in \"Cameras & Photo > Film Photography > Film Cameras\" or it can be dumped in \"Antiques > Decorative Arts > Other.\" The first category unlocks camera-specific item specifics (brand, film type, lens mount, condition) and puts you in front of buyers actively shopping for cameras. The second does neither."}]
1c:["$","p",null,{"children":"When in doubt about category, search for the top-selling comparable items and check what category they're listed in. If the highest-performing listings are consistently in the same subcategory, that's where you should be."}]
1d:["$","p",null,{"children":"eBay also allows dual-category listings for a fee. For items that genuinely straddle two audiences — a vintage camera that's also a collectible, a handmade item that's also a gift — the dual-category investment can meaningfully increase impressions."}]
1e:["$","h2",null,{"children":"4. Seller Performance Directly Affects Rank"}]
1f:["$","p",null,{"children":["Cassini is unusual among marketplace search engines in that it explicitly incorporates ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"seller performance metrics"}]," into ranking. Your defect rate, late shipment rate, cases closed without seller resolution, and positive feedback percentage all feed into your rank."]}]
20:["$","p",null,{"children":"This means two identical listings from two different sellers will rank differently based purely on seller health. An eBay seller with a 98.5% positive feedback rating and zero defects will outrank a similar seller with 96% feedback and occasional late shipments — even if both listings are identically optimized."}]
21:["$","div",null,{"className":"key-point","children":["$","p",null,{"children":"SEO on eBay is not just a listing-level activity. Maintaining strong seller metrics is table-stakes for ranking. Handle returns quickly, ship on time, and resolve disputes before they escalate."}]}]
22:["$","h2",null,{"children":"5. Use the Subtitle Field Strategically"}]
23:["$","p",null,{"children":["eBay offers a subtitle field (50 characters, small fee) that appears below your title in search results. It's ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"not indexed by Cassini for keyword purposes"}],", but it is visible to buyers — making it a conversion tool, not an SEO tool."]}]
24:["$","p",null,{"children":"Use the subtitle to add information that influences click-through: \"Free Shipping — Includes Original Box & Papers,\" \"Rare 1987 Edition — Only 3 Available,\" \"Trusted Seller — 5,000+ Positive Reviews.\" These add trust and urgency without cluttering your keyword-critical title."}]
25:["$","h2",null,{"children":"6. Description Matters for Google, Not Just eBay"}]
26:["$","p",null,{"children":"Cassini largely ignores your description for ranking purposes — but Google doesn't. eBay listings regularly appear in Google search results, and Google indexes your full description. This means a well-written, keyword-rich description can drive organic traffic from Google directly to your eBay listing."}]
27:["$","p",null,{"children":"Write your description for humans first — clear, detailed, and trustworthy — but front-load the key phrases. Cover the who (buyer: gift for dad, collector item), the what (exact product with attributes), the why (why buy this: condition, rarity, bundle value), and any relevant details that reduce buyer hesitation (returns policy, combined shipping)."}]
28:["$","div",null,{"className":"callout","children":[["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":12,"color":"#d0d0e8","fontWeight":700,"fontSize":"1.1rem"},"children":"Optimize your eBay listings without the research grind."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":20},"children":"TagMint rewrites your eBay listing titles and descriptions using real search data — so Cassini knows exactly what you're selling and buyers can actually find you. Fast turnaround, starting at $7."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/#pricing","className":"btn-primary px-7 py-3 text-sm","children":"See Pricing →"}]]}]
